<TEXT>
gerald bull a canadianborn arms 
dealer and weapons designer was killed in his home authorities 
say he was 62 
bull was shot to death thursday night in his apartpment in a 
fashionable suburb of brussels police said they have ruled out 
robbery as a motive because more than 20000 was found in bulls 
pockets 
bull was convicted in vermont in 1980 on charges of smuggling 
arms to south africa 
the canadian news agency southam news based in ottawa reported 
sunday that he had been working more recently with iraq to help it 
develop advanced weapons systems that were used in the iraniraq 
war 
he also had extensive business dealings with communist china 
southam reported 
the belgian newspaper derniere heure said bull had helped south 
africa develop the g5 longrange artillery gun the howitzertype 
guns were said to be more sophisticated than anything in either the 
nato or warsaw pact arsenals 
but in a statement issued to the belgian news agency bulls son 
stephen strongly denied that space research corp bulls company 
or its foreign affiliates were involved in arms dealing 
the space research corp has never been involved in 
activities breaking the arms embargo with south africa the 
statement said 
it said bull for several years had been involved in aeronautic 
and defense research 
bull was born in north bay ontario but gave up his canadian 
citizenship for a us passport sometime before 1977 the canadian 
embassy in brussels said 
once tabbed by macleans magazine as canadas boy genius of 
rocket science bull became in 1951 the youngest person to graduate 
from the university of toronto with a doctorate he was 22 
he first appeared on the vermont scene in 1967 when as a 
professor at mcgill university in montreal he established an 
aerospace science program at norwich university in northfield 
in 1970 bull began trying to perfect his plans to orbit nuclear 
warheads in space 
although he was canadian bull won access to highly classified 
american military files when the impropriety was discovered a 
special act of congress sponsored by sen barry goldwater rariz 
backdated his us citizenship application 
only two other aliens the marquis de lafayette and winston 
churchill have had such honorary citizenship bestowed upon them 
space research ran into trouble in the mid1970s when it failed 
to win the major military contracts it was seeking and lost a 12 
million contract to build 28 simulators for the federal aviation 
administration 
the companys demise came after us and canadian authorities 
and news media investigations found that it had struck a deal to 
sell advanced howitzer technology to the south african government 
in violation of us munitions laws and a united nations arms 
embargo against the white minorityruled country 
reports at the time indicated that the deal was accomplished 
through shipments through ports in antigua and spain commercial 
jet flights from new york and montreal and visits by space research 
engineers to a remote test range in south africa 
</TEXT>
