<TEXT>
dr boshigt this month became 
mongolias first communist party member to hand in his membership 
card ending a lifetime of waiting to speak out against political 
repression 
i had to wait for favorable conditions the 49yearold 
physician said in an interview speaking fluent english 
he had waited for decades 
boshigt joined the ruling mongolian peoples revolutionary party 
even though it had purged his physician father he worked for the 
semiofficial peace and friendship association acting as 
mongolias liaison to socialist international groups such as the 
africanasian solidarity committee 
for the scholarly softspoken boshigt as for many mongolians 
the time to speak came last fall 
with all this democratic change in east european countries and 
the perestroika policy this was the time to do something he 
said referring to the reform policies of soviet president mikhail 
s gorbachev 
boshigt who uses just one name said he met likeminded 
supporters of reform in this longtime soviet client state wedged 
between china and the soviet union he and the young intellectuals 
organized their first rally days later on international human 
rights day dec 10 
thus was born the mongolian democratic association the nations 
first opposition group in nearly seven decades 
always before there were people who wanted to do 
something the physician said it was impossible 
his father gongorjav was jailed for several years then 
banished to the countryside when he objected to replacing 
mongolias ancient script with the cyrillic letters used in the 
soviet union 
but voices of protest remained few and unorganized mongolia 
never developed a dissident community with its own literature and 
mutual support network 
that is why the speedy and effective organization of the 
democratic association came as such a surprise to mongolians by 
midmarch it claimed 70000 members in 17 branches nationwide and 
tens of thousands more supporters for its program of democratic 
reforms 
there is a scientific base a logic to the associations 
program said boshigt who became one of the groups chief 
strategists that is why we are going on so smoothly 
the only thing we accept from marxismleninism is its 
scientific methodology 
mongolias economic and political problems must be solved 
pragmatically he said resorting not to isms but a careful 
study of the countrys past much of which was labeled feudal and 
blotted out of history books by the communists 
mongolia had a basis for building a society we had political 
cultural religious traditions why should we cancel all that by 
building socialism 
determined to let young intellectuals take the lead boshigt 
stepped out of his mentor role only twice when he joined younger 
activists in a threeday hunger strike this month and when he 
turned in his party card 
they strongly criticized me in unen the party newspaper he 
said when the communists staged their own rally march 11 some 
carried a banner that read boshigt a traitor 
a second intellectual of boshigts generation economist p 
nerguye later followed suit many other ruling party members have 
kept their cards even while joining or helping the democratic 
association or other new opposition groups 
but the physician said he has not been harassed by authorities 
he dismissed younger association members dire predictions the 
government may still use force to crush the opposition 
the communists and the government they have long controlled have 
shuffled their top ranks in response to the opposition pressure 
but have yet to provide legal guarantees of political freedom 
boshigt said the communists remain strong with their control of 
the media and bureaucracy perhaps strong enough to win hopedfor 
multiparty elections this year 
but he said you cannot stop the young people because they 
really hate this stalinist regime there was no one i had to 
convince all were ready to give anything to end it 
</TEXT>
