<TEXT>
eight members of congress are trying to prove 
this year that you can go home again as governor 
potomac fever rarely goes into remission but among those 
politicians who have had enough of capitol hill an increasingly 
popular career path leads to places like little rock tallahassee 
hartford and montgomery 
seven members of congress won governorships from 1982 to 1989 
about a third of those who tried those odds are hardly comparable 
to the 98 percent return rate for members of congress who seek 
reelection but the higher risk hasnt discouraged a crop of eight 
new gubernatorial aspirants this year 
you can do more in an afternoon as governor than you can in a 
career in congress said one gubernatorial hopeful republican 
rep john rowland of connecticut attributing the quip to former 
delaware gov pete du pont 
it is theme sounded often among those hoping to return home 
many say they want to take on greater challenges test their 
executive skills set their own agendas and leave their marks on 
