with the auction of the last three available sections of the eiffel 
towers original spiral staircase 
the sale is to take place in toyko at the hotel okura and will 
be transmitted by satellite to bidders at the eiffel tower 
the staircase which links the second and third stories of the 
famed symbol of paris was inaugurated march 31 1889 when gustave 
eiffel climbed to the top and unfurled the french tricolor 
emblazoned with the gold initials rf for the french republic 
at the time the tower was the tallest structure ever built 
rising 1000 feet from its base the narrow winding staircase was 
the only way to the top 
in 1983 engineers had the staircase removed for security 
reasons the other sections of the staircase were sold earlier for 
prices ranging from 8500 to 25000 
