much less than a state 
predictably marcos supporters have been at the forefront of 
those who feel the trial infringes on sovereignty 
it is an insult to the countrys sovereignty because a former 
first lady deserves the dignity to defend herself in her own 
country said rep salvador escudero a member of marcos new 
society movement party whatever crime she has committed it 
should be defensible within the context of philippine laws 
but the trial also reminded other filipinos of the limitations 
of their own judicial system where proceedings are often 
influenced by money and political power the retrial of 40 
