<TEXT>
a hardline palestinian faction on monday 
openly challenged the plobacked leadership of the uprising and 
staged a wildcat strike widening a rift over tactics in the 
antiisraeli revolt 
the strike marked the anniversary of the egyptianisraeli peace 
treaty it was the latest act of defiance by the syrianbacked 
popular front for the liberation of palestine 
in two recent leaflets the group accused the three other 
factions in the leadership coalition of softening in their struggle 
against israeli occupation of the west bank and gaza strip 
palestinian activists who insisted on anonymity said contacts 
were under way to try to resolve the feud within the leadership of 
the 27monthold rebellion the leadership groups the popular front 
with yasser arafats fatah faction the palestine communist party 
and the democratic front for the liberation of palestine 
this is not the first time there have been differences and we 
were able in the past to surmount them one fatah activist said 
