john dexter a theater and opera director whose 
productions included such stage hits as equus and m 
butterfly as well as operas at covent garden and new yorks 
metropolitan opera house has died at age 64 
the times of london said his death friday in a london hospital 
was due to heart failure 
dexter was best known on broadway for his direction of equus 
in 1974 and m butterfly in 1988 both of which won him tony 
awards he made his broadway debut in 1963 with arnold weskers 
chips with everything 
among his other notable broadway productions were black 
comedy and the royal hunt of the sun both written by peter 
shaffer and do i hear a waltz the richard rodgersstephen 
sondheim musical 
dexters last broadway assignment was the illfated 3 penny 
opera starring rock idol sting which closed in december after a 
short run 
dexter began his theater career at the royal court in 1957 and 
then was asked by laurence olivier to join the national theater as 
an associate director there he directed othello with olivier 
playing the title role and maggie smith as desdemona among his 
other successes at the national were the misanthrope with alec 
mccowen and diana rigg hobsons choice and phaedra 
britannica with rigg 
