<TEXT>
moslems across the world scanned the 
skies after twilight monday in hopes of sighting the luminous 
crescent moon that heralds the festive but arduous dawntodusk 
fasting month of ramadan 
first to announce the sighting from the arabian peninsula was 
north yemen where a panel of islamic judges declared ramadan will 
start tuesday sightings also were reported in south yemen and 
saudi arabia who declared tuesday the start of the moslem holy 
month 
many of the worlds islamic nations automatically follow the 
saudi decision because the kingdom harbors islams holiest shrines 
ramadan is venerated by the worlds estimated 1 billion moslems 
as the month during which the archangel gabriel imparted the verses 
of the koran to mohammed the prophet of islam more than 14 
centuries ago it is the 9th month in the moslem lunar calendar 
for the 30 days of ramadan moslems must abstain from eating 
drinking and smoking from dawn to sunset they are to avoid 
pleasures of the flesh even an innocent kiss can be a violation 
the more devout will even avoid swallowing their own saliva 
only moslems who are traveling ill or pregnant during ramadan 
are exempt from the fast according to the koran but they must 
make up for this in subsequent months 
for weeks moslem countries stockpiled food in preparation for 
the nighttime feasts that follow the days of deprivation some 
scholars accuse moslems of turning ramadan into a month of feasting 
rather than fasting especially since many people actually gain 
weight 
moslems however say they achieve boundless spiritual gains 
during ramadan purifying their souls and giving themselves peace 
of mind 
tradition has it that the fast starts each day when a black 
thread can be distinguished from a white one and it ends when the 
two cannot be distinguished large cities often fire off a cannon 
to tell citizens when to stop and start eating 
the koran the holy book of islam prescribed fasting as one of 
the five pillars of the faith the others are to recognize the 
unitarian nature of allah and that mohammed is his prophet pray 
five times a day give alms and make the pilgrimage to mecca at 
least once 
the pillars are supposedly the primary factor that unite 
moslems but the fast has been manipulated by dissident factions 
and secular states to demonstrate divergent brands and practices of 
the same religion 
it is generally said that when the crescent is sighted in one 
moslem country with the naked eye other moslems everywhere in the 
world are required to observe the start of the fast 
however shiite moslem iran along with shiite communities in 
countries ruled by sunni moslems mark the start and end of ramadan 
ahead or behind the sunnis never on the same day 
turkey with a secular constitution has announced that ramadan 
commences wednesday under simple calendar count 
interior ministries along the persian gulf told nonmoslem 
citizens and expatriate workers to avoid eating drinking and 
smoking in public during ramadan 
moslems who eat drink or smoke publicly will be fine flogged 
and imprisoned the ministries warned 
liquor is strictly banned during ramadan and hotels are 
instructed to keep their restaurants shut between sunrise and 
sundown room service for foreigners however is permitted in most 
countries 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

