percent the radical liberal league of young democrats 857 percent 
and the christian democratic peoples party 643 percent 
the rest of the 29 parties that fielded candidates appeared to 
fall short of winning 4 percent of the vote nationwide and 
therefore would not be entitled to any parliament seats 
up to 14 candidates competed in most races and the vote was so 
split that many seats will have to be contested again election 
