<TEXT>
cmdr bradwell turner who led a daring rescue of 
299 seamen held prisoner on a german ship in 1940 has died 
according to a news report he was 92 
turner died last wednesday an obituary published in tuesdays 
edition of the times of london said no cause of death was given 
with a cry of the navys here turner led a boarding party 
from the destroyer hms cossack which freed the prisoners from the 
german supply ship altmark in a norwegian fjord in february 1940 
the altmark had been an auxiliary vessel of the german 
battleship graf spee seamen taken prisoner from merchant marine 
vessels sunk by the graf spee were put aboard the altmark 
the graf spee was scuttled just outside montevideo uruguay in 
december 1939 after being trapped by three british cruisers some 
of the graf spee survivors still reside in neighboring argentina 
after the elimination of the graf spee the altmark with its 
prisoners hid in the south atlantic for two months then in 
february it was sighted in norwegian waters 
pursuing british ships were intercepted by two norwegian torpedo 
boats whose commanders said the altmark had been inspected 
carried no arms and had no prisoners on board 
winston churchill then first lord of the admiralty ordered the 
navy to board the altmark and release the prisoners 
cossack entered the fjord on the night of feb 16 the skipper 
of the altmark steered straight at the british ship apparently 
intending to ram it but instead ran his own ship aground 
turner then a lieutenant commander led a boarding party 
carrying pistols and rifles four germans were killed and five were 
wounded in the encounter 
the rescue was an inspirational moment for the british who had 
little to show for their six months at war with germany 
turner received a distinguished service order in 1940 for his 
part in the action he received the order of the british empire in 
1951 
he served as a naval attache in oslo norway from 1954 to 1957 
and worked for the marconi electronics company from 1957 to 1972 
he is survived by his wife and three daughters 
