<TEXT>
albania has opened direct telephone service with the 
west lifting some of the restrictions that have made it one of the 
worlds most isolated countries 
an employee of the albanian telegraph agency in tirana 
albanias capital said direct telephone service between albania 
and some western countries began march 20 the operator was reached 
by directdial call from rome on monday 
the employee who did not give his name said 56 countries have 
directdial links with albania including the united states 
canada britain and france 
the operator said it was possible to call albania directly from 
france canada and britain and vice versa the operator said 
albanians may call the united states when asked if calls could be 
placed to albania from the united states the operator said i 
think so 
but attempts to do so monday were unsuccessful and rich 
wallerstein of american telephone amp telegraph co said the service 
was not yet in place 
beginning this past weekend it became possible for albanians 
to direct dial into the united states but we do not as yet have 
service from the united states to albania he said 
wallerstein said the albanian telegraph agency and atampt had been 
discussing establishing service for some time 
the way it came to our attention was albanians were phoning 
relatives in the united states and people in the united states 
tried to phone back and couldnt get through he said 
albania a country of 32 million people is europes last 
bastion of stalinist isolation it has pursued orthodox 
marxistleninist policies since the communists took over in 1944 
but there have been increased signs of openings to the west 
under president ramiz alia who took over after the death of enver 
hoxha in 1985 
some western journalists have been allowed into albania in 
recent months they reported seeing apartment houses with homemade 
antennas to receive tv broadcasts from italy greece and yugoslavia 
alitalia italys flag airline started a weekly flight to 
albania last year olympic airways the greek airline also flies 
to albania 
the italian government signed a wideranging economic 
cooperation agreement with albania last year that will also involve 
the country in regional efforts to clean up the adriatic sea 
before americans can call albania financial and technical 
hurdles must be cleared wallerstein said us telephone companies 
must get paid a share for the calls placed to and from albania and 
a directdial system must be established 
albania currently places calls to western countries though 
relays in either greece or italy wallerstein said 
