the fiji times newspaper said ola stillman rockefeller was 
injured on saturday soon after he arrived at laucala island about 
120 miles northeast of fijis capital suva 
the isolated resort is owned by the estate of the late american 
billionaire malcolm forbes 
rockefeller a bachelor told the newspaper he had been swimming 
alone in waistdeep water about 30 yards offshore when he felt his 
right leg being pulled 
looking down he said he saw it had been lacerated apparently 
by two bites from a shark 
he said he managed to swim to shore and crawl to his bungalow 
where he telephoned for help 
resort workers applied firstaid before a nurse from a village 
health clinic could assist a doctor from a nearby hospital was 
brought in by boat several hours later 
on arrival dr viliame taoi said he found rockefeller in stable 
condition but he appeared to have lost some blood his 
achilles tendon had been lacerated and required stiches 
at dawn sunday rockefeller was flown by the forbes private 
plane to a hospital in lautoka fijis secondlargest city 
he left fiji on an overnight flight to the united states 
accompanied by a medical team from australia and with his right 
ankle in a plaster cast 
i have not been discouraged by the experience he was quoted 
as telling the fiji times newspaper before departing 
rockefeller is the grandson of james s rockefeller who was a 
chairman of the city bank of new york which became citibank 
michael rockefeller son of thennew york gov nelson d 
rockfeller vanished in november 1961 off irian jaya an 
indonesian territory that shares its island border with papua new 
guinea 
michael then 23 disappeared while swimming from his capsized 
catamaran in sharkinfested waters the island of irian jaya and 
papua new guinea is about 1000 miles west of fiji 
