we estimate that from 65000 to 70000 people died in the 
internment camps of the soviet occupying powers after world war 
ii finn told saarlandischer rundfunk radio in saarbruecken 
finn is the author of a book on the subject titled political 
prisoners in the soviet zone 
he said it would be impossible to give an exact figure because 
all death certificates of the camps were destroyed 
