the citys requirement that news 
agencies sign an embargo agreement before obtaining an advance copy 
of material for a news conference could set a dangerous precedent 
a media law specialist said 
the mayors office would not release an internal police report 
on the custody of mob informant peter gilbert before the march 22 
news conference unless reporters signed a lengthy embargo agreement 
material commonly is embargoed but reporters are not required 
to sign such contracts 
to my knowledge its unprecedented said thomas a schwartz 
a media law specialist at ohio state university 
historically there has been a matter of trust between media 
sources and the media he said but im sure that many media 
sources have been burned in recent times and have become more 
cautious in protecting the release of such material 
the contract acknowledged the 280page report would be 
