creators of an ambitious multimedia effort 
targeting hispanics say 90 percent of the 10 million in annual ad 
time and space was sold as the service debuted march 26 
the service will reach an estimated 500000 hispanic magazine 
readers and nearly 90 percent of hispanic homes with television 
says its developer whittle communications of knoxville tenn 
starting later this spring advertisers also will be mentioned 
when operators answer calls to a tollfree telephone service for 
hispanics seeking information on topics ranging from recipes to 
immigration the operator will answer calls by saying the hotline 
service is brought to you by 
sponsors pay 500000 a year under twoyear contracts for a 
basic package that includes television telephone time and magazine 
space those who have signed so far include american airlines 
procter amp gamble american telephone amp telegraph and kinney shoes 
whittle says 
the cornerstone of the service is the magazine la familia de 
hoy published every other month it is distributed free to 10500 
medical waiting rooms and beauty parlors in hispanic neigborhoods 
in 45 markets 
whittle is also producing twominute informational programs that 
will run 31 times a week on the spanishlanguage television network 
univision which reaches 64 million spanishspeaking households in 
the united states 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
