newspapers owner of six similar publications in michigan the 
newspapers which feature and promote us carmaking have a 
combined circulation of 41000 
a monthly trade publication nashville automotive reports 
already is published in middle tennessee and automotive news 
maintains a bureau here 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
with headlines like human lotto balls bounce to 
new heights the illinois state lottery has produced a quarterly 
with everything inquiring minds want to know about the game 
jackpot circulation 2 million is an eightpage tabloid with 
color graphs cartoons and stories and lots of pictures of lottery 
players and employees 
its distributed free to lottery agents and outlets where game 
tickets are sold 
jackpot is meant to help fill the gap lottery officials feel was 
left when the daily press grew accustomed to the weekly games now 
in their 16th year said editor mary johnstonclark 
at the beginning a 5 million lotto jackpot was big she 
said adding that illinois newspapers and broadcasters were excited 
about the subject 
now only the big jackpots get much press notice 
now unless its 20 million or 30 million or 40 million 
they dont bat an eye 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
a top gamingindustry analyst says he 
was fired march 23 for remarks he made to the wall street journal 
about donald trumps newest casino 
marvin roffman an analyst for 16 years with janney montgomery 
scott in philadelphia said his company was angry about remarks he 
made to the journal in a story about the taj mahal casino resort 
scheduled to open april 2 
roffman said the quotes which said trump would have difficulty 
meeting the debt service on the property were accurate although 
many other favorable quotes about the casino were omitted 
roffman said trump forced the company to make him issue a letter 
of public apology roffman who was widely quoted in casino 
stories said he also was forced to take a pay cut and never talk 
again to reporters 
roffman said he later had second thoughts and faxed another 
letter to trump saying the first letter contained many 
inaccuracies he said the second letter cost him his job because 
the company told him not to write it 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the political writer for boston universitys 
bostonia magazine lost his job after submitting a column critical 
of the school presidents political campaign 
john r silber is on leave as president while seeking the 
democratic nomination for governor 
bostonia is subsidized by the university and is distributed free 
to alumni and sold to the public 
martin s goldman the magazines political columnist for three 
years said march 22 his firing raises questions of censorship 
keith botsford who was appointed publisher and editorinchief 
of the magazine by silber last summer said goldman had been told 
not to write about local politics 
botsford said it would be illegal for the magazine to take sides 
because the university is a taxexempt nonprofit corporation 
i would have done it if it was about evelyn murphy or anyone 
else he said lt gov evelyn murphy also seeks the democratic 
nomination for governor 
i expect to take a beating in the press for this it will look 
like censorship but it isnt any reasonable editor would have 
done the same 
he said silber was unaware of the incident and goldman said 
i dont see silbers hand in it 
</TEXT>
