<TEXT>
a hollywood studio representative and nbctv 
exchanged verbal brickbats march 23 over a network program dealing 
with a new hollywood where small producers are likely to get 
squashed by large competitors 
jack valenti president of the motion picture association of 
america said he was outraged over nbcs the new hollywood 
broadcast march 21 
valenti said nbc failed to disclose its own efforts in 
washington to wrest back control of its programs from hollywood 
producers 
tom brokaw who anchored the program called valentis attack an 
insult to his journalistic integrity 
valenti in a letter to nbc president robert wright demanded a 
opportunity in television prime time to present a rebuttal to 
nbcs lack of disclosure 
nbc spokesman joe rutledge said valentis demand was idiotic 
that means no 
hollywood producers including the major studios that make up 
the mpaa have been involved in negotiations for seven years over 
federal rules that prevent abc nbc and cbs from having a financial 
interest in the programs they broadcast or from selling those 
programs in the lucrative us rerun market 
valenti emphasized that he was not questioning brokaws 
integrity 
he said his quarrel with nbc was its failure to disclose that it 
was in a political struggle and a regulatory struggle with the 
studios it was criticizing 
</TEXT>
