<TEXT>
zapnews a lowcost news service to be 
distributed to radio and television stations via fax machines and 
personal computers will begin operations april 2 the company said 
march 20 
zapnews founder james r hood said the company will distribute 
news sports and features over dialup longdistance telephone 
lines it subscribes to the reuters and sportsticker wires and is 
forming a network of correspondents of its own hood said 
the agency will begin supplying state and regional news 
gradually over the next 18 months from headquarters in fairfax 
county va in the suburbs of washington 
hood was general broadcast editor and deputy director of 
broadcast services for the associated press leaving in 1986 after 
14 years with the company after leaving the ap he served for a 
time as vice president for broadcast services of united press 
international 
hood said zapnews subscribers would pay only for the scripts 
they order his announcement at the national press club in 
washington did not quote prices 
</TEXT>
