<TEXT>
a sacramento lawyer has been appointed 
as the first executive director of the california first amendment 
coalition responsible for offering advice in gaining access to 
public institutions 
terry franke will assume his new duties in april according to a 
statement released march 20 by mel opotowsky president of the 
coalition and senior managing editor of the pressenterprise in 
riverside 
franke has served as legal counsel for the california newspaper 
publishers association in sacramento since 1980 he has gained 
recognition as an authority on the publics right to attend 
government meetings review public records and observe court 
proceedings 
as executive director he will operate a public hotline 
service and also will direct a membership and resources development 
program that is expected to include a series of educational 
seminars and other services 
the coalition was formed in 1988 by journalism organizations 
concerned about the way public officials ignored state and federal 
laws requiring open meetings and access to government records 
</TEXT>
