<TEXT>
from cats to nicholas nickleby to 
aspects of love trevor nunn is among the worlds most 
successful and soughtafter directors of both plays and musicals 
but blockbuster shows constitute only one aspect of his eclectic 
career shakespeares plays ts eliots verse a musical about 
chess an obscure english novel everything is fodder for nunns 
vision of the stage as a great populist meeting place 
im interested in theater in all its forms and theater 
audiences in all their forms the bearded 50yearold director 
said one evening after work at his office in londons theater 
district where he has four musicals running at the same time 
cats based on the ts eliot poems has been running since 
1981 starlight express a show that casts actors as trains 
opened in 1984 les miserables the victor hugo 
novelturnedmusical codirected by john caird followed in 1985 
and last year came aspects of love based on a littleknown 
1950s english novel about the complex entanglements of five lovers 
but for 18 years he also headed or coheaded the royal 
shakespeare company one of britains two major statesubsidized 
theaters he left it in 1986 but retains the title director 
emeritus 
accordingly his credits present an intriguing mix of romeo 
and juliet and rollerskating trains hedda gabler and 
anthropomorphized cats aspects and alls well that ends 
well les miserables and macbeth 
i dont like categories i dont like signatures says nunn 
defining a career that began at cambridge university where he 
directed the footlights revue 
i dont see any disparity between different types of work to 
have eclecticism only requires a theater community with sufficient 
variety and sufficient promotion of that variety 
whether directing the bard in stratforduponavon or a mammoth 
musical on broadway nunn feels theres no point in doing it for 
the critics or the already converted 
but its musicals that have given nunn fame and wealth most 
often in conjunction with composer andrew lloyd webber 
in 1981 they paired up on a song cycle of eliots old 
possums poems for practical cats which lloyd webber thought 
might make a charming childrens entertainment 
theater insiders were disdainful but the result was cats 
currently purring its way toward a gross of over 460 million in 
the united states alone 
nunn says the show married a love of language to his 
longstanding interest in musicals indeed he had turned down 
several previous offers that didnt seem right including 42nd 
street on broadway which he felt an american should do 
during cats rehearsals lloyd webber gave nunn a copy of the 
1955 novel aspects of love by david garnett nine years later 
their musical version still running in london is now playing at 
the broadhurst theater in new york 
the show concerns a lovestruck quintet pursuing their 
emotionally dangerous liaisons in the south of france four of its 
stars originated their parts on the west end 
michael ball a briton making his broadway debut plays alex an 
english army recruit whose love for a french actress ann crumb 
shapes his entire life kevin colson is alexs dilettantish uncle 
george kathleen rowe mcallen plays georges italian mistress 
giulietta 
its a piece of work interested in character and the 
character is artfully and cleverly and touchingly presented nunn 
says 
as production costs rise on broadway and critical pressures 
mount lloyd webber is one of the few theater artists whose 
boxoffice clout makes him impervious to the reviews which can be 
harsh 
nunns career has ridden its own critical roller coaster in 
london plaudits have been tempered with accusations that he has 
sold out to the commercial theater sacrificing firstrate work in 
the classics for the ready money of the major musical on broadway 
both starlight express and chess were poorly received 
many of the things ive done have run long periods of time no 
thanks to critical reactions which were frequently very hostile 
he says therefore i have every reason to trust the general 
public 
by and large that public has confirmed his trust nicholas 
nickleby an adaptation of the charles dickens novel opened to 
lukewarm reviews in london in 1980 then became a popular favorite 
on both sides of the atlantic despite a broadway top ticket of 
100 
les miserables adapted from victor hugos epic novel got 
mixed reviews at its 1985 london bow but swept the 1987 tony 
awards on broadway and won international acclaim 
occasionally nunn misjudges his staging of chess the tim 
riceabba musical ran more than three years on the west end but a 
scant 10 weeks on broadway in 1988 a broadway revival of 
nicholas nickleby also flopped 
in january nunns london production of the american musical 
the bakers wife closed after 56 performances at a loss of 
almost 17 million 
its flop was very disappointing denting as well as 
daunting he says 
the musical starred his second wife australian performer sharon 
lee hill in the lead role the couple who met when she appeared 
in cats have two daughters he has a son by his previous wife 
actress janet suzman 
away from the highstakes world of musicals nunn continues to 
mount landmark productions of the classics last fall he returned 
to the royal shakespeare company to stage othello with opera 
singer willard white as the jealous moor and ian mckellen as his 
nemesis iago 
nunn has also triumphed with more obscure shakespeare works his 
1982 alls well that ends well seen in london and new york 
made one of the bards socalled problem plays hauntingly clear 
and poignant 
plans for the future include another collaboration with david 
edgar who adapted nicholas nickleby and a staging of 
shakespeares twelfth night which nunn calls one of the 
unassailable masterpieces of the western world 
</TEXT>
