<TEXT>
gold prices plummeted as much as 30 an ounce 
monday in hectic selling linked to the dollars strength and 
intensified by rumors of heavy sales by large international 
investors 
another dollar advance against the japanese yen stoked the 
bearish attitude toward gold that has been building for weeks 
several negative forces joined to jolt gold an unconfirmed 
report of a huge sale by saudi arabia plus rumored selling by 
japanese and soviet parties had a domino effect on precious metals 
markets as other investors dumped gold to beat further price 
declines 
my guess is that theres been pretty widespread selling 
based on a technically bearish chart picture and expectations of 
continued strength in the us dollar which has been the main 
culprit in golds weakness for several weeks said jeffrey a 
nichols president of american precious metals advisors inc in 
toronto 
