philips display components co said 
monday it will build a 100 million television picture tube plant 
at saline about 10 miles south of its ann arbor headquarters 
construction will start in july on the plant aimed at keeping 
the subsidiary of dutch electronics giant nv philips in the 
highdefinition television race it will be completed early in 
1992 said dr iva wilson philips display components president 
the 400000squarefoot plant is designed to produce 1 million 
27inch color picture tubes a year and make hdtv tubes in the 
future 
philips display components is the top maker of picture tubes 
with 70 percent of its production going to philips consumer 
electronics products including the magnavox sylvania and philco 
television brands 
it also provides tubes for television makers such as sharp 
toshiba nec jvc hitachi mic and the korean gold star and 
samsung brands 
the company moved its headquarters last year from seneca falls 
ny the ann arbor facility develops products for manufacture at a 
plant in ottawa ohio 
the new plant wont affect operations at the ottawa facility 
which employs about 2000 people wilson said 
the picture tubes are assembled into televisions by another 
subsidiary philips consumer electronics in greenville tenn 
the federal communications commission said last week it expected 
to set a standard for hdtv broadcasting by spring 1993 
hdtv produces a sharper video image than conventional television 
and compactdisc quality sound 
the fcc said it favored systems sending hdtv signals on separate 
channels from conventional programming 
philips consumer electronics said in january it was entering 
into a joint venture with a unit of frances thomson sa and the 
national broadcasting co to look at such a system 
zenith electronics corp the last major usbased television 
maker is working with american telephone amp telegraph co on that 
type of system 
