gold futures prices were swamped monday by a tidal wave of 
selling that apparently began in the middle east and swept through 
markets around the world eroding prices to their lowest levels in 
more than five months 
on other commodity markets soybean futures surged grains were 
higher copper futures fell pork bellies rose sharply while 
livestock futures were mixed and energy futures were mixed 
gold futures settled 2320 to 25 lower on new yorks commodity 
exchange with the contract for delivery in april at 36620 a troy 
ounce the lowest gold settlement price on the exchange since oct 
13 
silver futures prices fell 88 cents to 107 cents in new york 
with the march contract settling at 4955 a troy ounce the first 
close below 5 since mid1986 
analysts agreed the collapse was sparked by an overseas sale of 
as much as 1 million ounces of gold bullion a huge amount by a 
single source 
rumors were rampant but many experts traced the initial sale to 
the saudi arabian monetary agency or to a commercial bank in saudi 
arabia that may have sold gold and bought british pounds 
another view was that china was the initial seller exchanging 
gold for hard currency 
major investors quickly followed suit analysts said pouring up 
to 2 million more ounces of gold onto the market 
we had three million ounces hitting the market at a time it 
was structurally a little weak anyway and knocked it all to 
hell said george millingstanley first vice president in charge 
of bullion sales at shearson lehman hutton inc 
spot gold prices fell sharply amid heavy selling in zurich 
switzerland and panic selling in london before the new york 
market opened said don tierney an analyst with stanley bell amp co 
in new york 
at midday the commodity exchange announced it was raising by 
700 to 2100 the speculative margin or downpayment needed to 
play the gold market forcing further selling by traders who could 
not afford the extra margin 
tierney said some traders who would normally have been rolling 
their positions out of the soontoexpire april contract and into 
the june contract chose instead to get out of the market entirely 
to see how far this thing is going to go 
some experts predicted a rebound on tuesday but opinions varied 
greatly 
peter cardillo commodity trading adviser with josephthal amp co 
said the market was oversold but he also said that the fact the 
april contract closed below its previous low of 370 is not a 
healthy sign 
soybean futures rose strongly on the chicago board of trade 
after an expected crush of brazilian soybean exports failed to 
materialize grain futures also advanced 
the soybean market had sold off sharply friday on speculation 
that economic reforms aimed at stemming brazils runaway inflation 
rate would be implemented over the weekend causing soybean exports 
to resume after a weeklong lull 
