<TEXT>
north american philips corp said it has entered 
into an agreement to sell a division that makes toothbrushes and 
cosmetics packaging products to a buyout firm 
under the deal announced monday terms of which were not 
disclosed philips will sell anchor advanced products inc to 
anchor acquisition corp a company formed by thomas h lee co and 
members of the divisions management thomas h lee is a 
bostonbased private investment firm 
anchor advanced products is the worlds largest toothbrush 
maker according to philips the north american arm of the dutch 
electronics giant nv philips 
</TEXT>
