<TEXT>
norwest corp has received approval from the 
federal reserve to acquire first interstate corp of wisconsin 
under the agreement announced in september first interstate 
shareholders will receive norwest stock with a value of about 215 
million 
first interstate wisconsins fifthlargest bank holding 
company has 1250 employees and assets of more than 17 billion 
under the acquisition sheboyganbased first interstate will 
become norwestwisconsin 
minneapolisbased norwest the states largest bank has assets 
of about 243 billion 
norwest spokesman larry haeg said no other regulatory approvals 
are needed first interstate shareholders also have approved the 
deal which is scheduled to close about may 1 haeg said 
norwest also plans to expand with the acquisition of the 
50branch first minnesota savings bank of minneapolis under a deal 
announced in late february regulatory approval also is required 
for that transaction 
</TEXT>
